                      NGST Observatory Designs Overview



   The following table shows the current parameters for the NGST
   observatory strawman designs from each of the federally funded Phase A
   studies. Additional information about the GSFC design is publicly
   available either on our web site or by request. All designs would be
   capable of being launched in 2008 with an Atlas IIAS-class priced
   vehicle ($100M) available in that time frame.  (You can click on the
   images of the telescopes to download a high resolution image of each.)
   __________________________________________________________________


   CAPTION: NGST Strawman design parameters

   Property TRW/Ball Aerospace GSFC Lockheed-Martin
    Configuration Ball Aerospace NGST concept image
   Hi-re images GSFC design

   Hi-res: JPEG file
   Lockheed-Martin design

   Hi-re images
    Primary mirror diameter (m) >8.0 8.0 8.0
    Orbit L2 Lissajous L2 Halo L2 Halo
    Mission lifetime 10 years 10 years 10 years
    Wavelength Coverage 0.6-30 µm 0.6-30 µm 0.6-32 µm
    Point Source Sensitivity [nJy]
    (10,000 sec, R~5, S/N=10)    1 nanoJansky=31.4 AB
   magnitudes
    1 micron  2.5  3 3.7
    2 micron  2.6  3 2.1
    3 micron  2.2  3 1.9
    5 micron  9.9 12 7.6
    10 micron  119  181 130
    20 micron  411 1570 1000
    NIR Camera FOV 4' x 4' 4' x 4' 4' x 4'
    NIR Spectrometer 3' x 3', MOS 3' x 3', MOS 3' x 3' MOS
    TIR Camera FOV 2' x 2' 2' x 2' 2' x 2'
    TIR Spectrometer Slit Slit Slit
    Diffraction Limit 2.0 micron 2.2 micron 2.0 micron
    NIR pixel scale  0.029"/pixel  0.029"/pixel  0.029"/pixel
    TIR pixel scale  0.230"/pixel  0.230"/pixel 0.121"/pixel
    Observatory mass (kg) EELV - medium compatible 2480 3600
    1 year sky coverage  ~100%  ~100%  ~100%

                          LM reference architecture

   MOS = Multi-object spectrograph
